                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/111: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MWJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 7, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Department’s 31, February 27, 2 p.m. What are the developments in this matter
                    and what, if any, steps are being taken to put the Government of Salvador on a
                    basis where recognition can be extended to it consistently with the provisions
                    of the 1923 Treaty?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
